    "eyebrow": "Cultural Influences",
    "num": "01",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">01</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Influences</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Spanish Colonial Legacy in Texican Culture</h2><ul><li>Spanish colonization introduced language, religion, and legal systems</li><li>Catholicism shaped community rituals and festivals</li><li>Land grant system influenced settlement patterns</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Spanish colonial period laid foundational cultural elements for Texicans, including language, religion, and land tenure practices that persisted into the 19th century. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Many Texican families maintained Catholic traditions such as patron saint festivals, reflecting Spanish religious influence.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify how Spanish legal and religious systems might have shaped Texican community life.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texican culture was purely Mexican without recognizing Spanish colonial roots.</p></div></div>",
