    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">07</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Practices</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Social and Family Life</h2><ul><li>Extended family networks central to social organization</li><li>Community events rooted in Catholic and indigenous traditions</li><li>Economic activities tied to land and livestock shaped daily routines</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican social life revolved around family and community, blending religious and indigenous customs with frontier economic realities. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Family gatherings often coincided with religious festivals and communal ranch work.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Describe how Texican family and community life reflected their cultural synthesis.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Separating economic life from cultural and social practices.</p></div></div>",
