    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">08</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Distinctions</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Differentiating Texicans from Anglo Settlers</h2><ul><li>Language: Spanish predominated among Texicans, English among Anglos</li><li>Legal traditions: Mexican land and family laws vs. Anglo common law</li><li>Cultural customs: Texican Catholicism vs. Anglo Protestantism</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans maintained distinct cultural markers that set them apart from Anglo settlers arriving in Texas during the 19th century. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican land inheritance laws differed significantly from Anglo practices, affecting property distribution.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Compare and contrast Texican and Anglo cultural traits in early Texas.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming cultural assimilation was immediate or complete.</p></div></div>",
