    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">12</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Transition</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">From Culture to Settlement: Next Steps</h2><ul><li>Understanding cultural background sets context for settlement patterns</li><li>Settlement influenced by land grants, geography, and frontier challenges</li><li>Next section explores Texican lifestyle and economic activities</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Having established the cultural foundations, learners will next examine where and how Texicans settled and lived in early Texas. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Land grant locations often determined Texican ranching communities.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Prepare to analyze primary sources on Texican settlement and daily life.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Separating cultural identity from settlement context.</p></div></div>",
