    "eyebrow": "Primary Source Workshop",
    "num": "14",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">14</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Source Workshop</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Analyzing Texican Legal Documents</h2><ul><li>Review land grants and legal petitions from Texican settlers (s12, s15).</li><li>Understand how Texicans navigated Mexican and later Texan legal systems.</li><li>Identify claims reflecting cultural and political identity.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Legal documents reveal how Texicans asserted rights and negotiated identity within shifting political frameworks, illustrating their agency and contested allegiances. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A land grant petition shows a Texican appealing to Mexican authorities, emphasizing loyalty while asserting property rights.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Interpret a legal petition excerpt to determine how Texicans balanced cultural identity with political pragmatism.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking the strategic nature of legal language as a tool for survival rather than pure ideological expression.</p></div></div>",
