    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">16</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Source Analysis</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Military Correspondence</h2><ul><li>Examine letters and orders from Texican military leaders (s10, s16).</li><li>Identify expressions of loyalty and strategic priorities.</li><li>Note how military roles influenced identity and political stance.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Military correspondence reveals how Texicans balanced personal, cultural, and political identities during conflict, providing insight into their role in the Texas Revolution. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A letter from a Texican officer expresses commitment to Texan independence while acknowledging Mexican heritage.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze a military letter to determine how Texican leaders framed their allegiance and objectives.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the influence of military context on identity expressions.</p></div></div>",
